snippet.textDisplay: I have to admit that although I really enjoy all these videos, I am not really a modern car fan per se. I watch more to keep up to date with the best in modern road machinery and to enjoy seeing Shmee so enthusiastically enjoying himself so much with his modern hi-tech toys. Anyone who is happy with their lot makes me happy too, even though I personally can't even afford to run any car at all myself and even struggle to pay my council rates and electricity bills! I have always been a classic BMW fan (2002 through to 635i to E30 M3 era) however all that said, this new M8 in that beautiful green even has me enthusiastic about the car itself. What a beautiful colour - reminds me of the colours we used to happily put on cars back when I was young in the early 1970s.  And yes, the headlight contrast - wonderful. The only thing I am not quite as enthusiastic about are these newest generation BMW grills. I kind of liked the more subtle ones. They almost look like what I would expect from Korean cars rather than European ones.
